could help to flip certain swingy, ag-heavy districts in Iowa, Minnesota, N=
ebraska, or elsewhere from the Republicans=E2=80=99 to the Democrats=E2=80=
=99 side.=C2=A0<br/><br/><strong>Angie Craig</strong>, the Democratic ranki=
ng member on House Ag, is now signaling that the demands for cuts might imp=
